Table \@ref(tab:summary) shows the summary accounts for local authorities in Wales of the incomes and expenditures arising from parking charges and penalty income both for on- and off-street parking. The income has increased by 116.9 %, the expenditure has increased by 8.7 % and the surplus has fallen by 191.2 % compared to the previous fiscal year. Total transport expenditure has fallen by 5.0 % and the surplus now represents 2.9 % of net transport epxenditure. Since 2017-18 income has fallen by 4.0 % and expenditure has risen by 18.5 %. Over the same period the surplus has fallen by 41.7 %. Figure \@ref(fig:fig1) gives a longer term overview of the trends in incomes, expenditures and surpluses.

