# Surpluses

Table \@ref(tab:surplustab) shows the parking surpluses from from 2017-18 to 2021-22 and the change from 2020-21 to 2021-22. It also shows the proportion that parking surpluses represent of total transport expenditure.

The total *surpluses* for Wales amounted to £10.2 million between 15 authorities of which Swansea, Gwynedd, and Conwy contributed 43.7%.

\`Seven councils made a loss with the total of parking deficits falling to £1.8 million from £9.5 million last year.

Overall, parking contributed £8.4 million to local authority finances in Wales in 2021-22 compared with £-9.2 million in 2021-22, an increase of NA %.

Swansea increased their surplus by 17349.5 % while Gwynedd and NA increased by 377.2 % and NA % respectively. The biggest decreases were in Gwynedd (377.2 %), and Swansea (17349.5 %).

The largest increase of deficit was incurred by Torfaen which increased their deficit by 33.4 % 

